    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.13a" />
                
                <note type="curatorial">551 Neihardt Collection</note>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">13a</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead"> 
                    <hi rend="caps">NEW YORK STATE COLLEGE OF AGRICULTURE
                        <lb/>
                    CORNELL UNIVERSITY
                        <lb/>
                    ITHACA, NEW YORK
                        <lb/>
                    
                    DEPARTMENT OF AGRICULTURAL ECONOMICS
                        <lb/>
                    WARREN HALL</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>april 18, 1958</dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear John: -</salute></opener> <p>Just a line to ask you for the <hi rend="underline">title of</hi> your performance here. We shall need it for the posters and press release. I always like for these to be prepared well ahead of time. You will know how to describe the lyrics that you plan to present.</p>
                
                <p>As for Thompson's class, I feel sure that The Death of Crazy Horse Would be excellent. The students who heard you give that have all left the University.</p>
                
                <note type="authorial">I have just confirmed this, Thompson says that this would be <hi rend="underline">excellent</hi>, the very best. You will have the entire 50 minutes.</note>
                
                <p>After the long winter and the whiteness of the world, the wave of spring is now dashing high over these hills leaving its green spray on the tallest tree as well as the lowliest bush. And theres something in the feel of the air. Again the miracle of reviving <del/> life lifts the <unclear>soul</unclear>. The <unclear>sap</unclear> is rising. It will be wonderful to have you here, my dear friend, and to look after you</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>affectionately,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Slade</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript>
                    <opener><hi rend="caps">P.S.</hi></opener> <p>It is fine that the new honor, election to the post of Fellow in the Institute of Arts &amp; Letters, has come to you.</p>
                    
                    <p>May the stable venture turn out well for Alice.</p>
                </postscript>    
                
            </div1>
